expert_text: In hypoxic pulmonary hypertension (WHO Group III), the low levels of oxygen are thought to cause vasoconstriction or tightening of pulmonary arteries.

expert_text: Arterial blood carries oxygen from inhaled air to all of the cells of the body, and venous blood carries carbon dioxide, a waste product of metabolism by cells, to the lungs to be exhaled.

expert_text: The kinetoplastids (also known as ` kinetoplastea ') are a group of single-cell flagellate protozoa, including a number of parasites responsible for serious diseases in humans and other animals, as well as various forms found in soil and aquatic environments.

model_output: Kinetoplastids are single-celled flagellates, which are a type of protozoan. Some of them are parasites that cause diseases in animals and humans, while others live in the soil or in water and do not cause any problems.
